# --- Video strategy (rewritten 2026-04-21 after homepage videos went dark) ---
#
# Background: On 2026-04-20 a nuclear `*.mp4 / *.mov / *.webm` rule was added
# after GitHub rejected the 147MB Solik push. That rule stripped EVERY video
# from the repo — GitHub Actions deploys from git, so Firebase Hosting
# immediately served 404s for every <video> on jegodigital.com.
#
# Fix: ignore by SIZE, not by extension. Videos under GitHub's 100MB file cap
# live in git and ship to Firebase Hosting via the deploy pipeline. Anything
# larger is blocked per-file by name AND pre-push hook
# (scripts/check-large-files.sh, flags any >90MB blob in `git diff --cached`).
#
# The top-level /videos/ folder is a Remotion dev project with node_modules —
# never ship its raw sources; finished renders are copied into website/videos/.

# Remotion dev project at repo root (source + node_modules + intermediate renders)
/videos/
!videos/*.webm
!videos/*.mov

# Specific per-file excludes for anything that has exceeded the 90MB threshold.
# Add new lines here when a new master render tops the limit; do NOT go back
# to extension wildcards. Each entry is a conscious "host this elsewhere"
# decision — not a blanket ban.
# (currently: all referenced assets fit under the limit, nothing excluded)

.secrets/

# Imported skill docs — many SKILL.md files contain embedded API keys
# for internal use (Perplexity, ElevenLabs, Meta, YouTube, etc). These
# must NEVER be pushed to GitHub. GitHub secret scanner blocks the push
# anyway. Added 2026-04-20 after push was rejected by GH013 secret scanner.
_imported_skills/
skill-packages/
.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/notebooklm/
